    "16560502492171dd33": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "c17791aa-99c0-44b1-9c0e-b600e8c2dd36": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Get the police involved",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "16560502493ef96db8-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If nothing up to this point has worked, then you can call the police to file a complaint. You can let the police know that you have taken steps to solve the situation but haven’t been successful. They can then investigate and take action if they see fit.<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "9cf025d1-5938-49bb-88c5-4141d8af1b5c": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "File a lawsuit",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "76ff5268-049f-4343-93b3-691311723d4c": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If the police fail to make a difference, the final step would be to file a lawsuit in a small claims court. You will need to provide evidence of the noise, the steps you previously took, and a testimony. If successful, a court order will be imposed on your neighbors, forcing them to cease the excessive noise.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "c17791aa-99c0-44b1-9c0e-b600e8c2dd36",
        "16560502493ef96db8-0",
